M/I Schottenstein Homes Inc. said Irving E. Schottenstein and Melvin L. Schottenstein, executive officers and principal stockholders, proposed a $7-a-share buy-out of the company. 

The home builder said the company would provide $2.3 million while Schottenstein families fund $5.1 million to purchase the remaining 1.1 million shares of the company's common stock.
The Schottenstein families currently own 4.7 million shares. 

The company said the proposal was submitted to an independent committee of the board.
If approved by the committee, the transaction would be submitted to shareholders for approval. 

